{
  "text": "In recent years, with the development of satellite remote sensing technology, it has become possible to study the interaction between clouds, precipitation and aerosols through satellites. The continuous observation of satellites can provide information on clouds, precipitation and aerosols worldwide. Through these data research and analysis, it is actually verified that the precipitation will decrease with the increase of aerosol. Huang to study the effect of aerosol on stratocumulus clouds. In the case of a certain liquid-water path in the cloud, the increase in aerosol can reduce the cloud droplet size. [CITATION_1] analyzed MODIS data and station precipitation data, and pointed that the increase in aerosol caused the decrease in precipitation in eastern China.",
  "citation_candidates": [
